.TH SUTURE-MERGE "1" "April 2026" "Suture v5.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
suture\-merge \- Merge a branch into the current branch
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suture merge [\\fIoptions\\fR] \\fIsource\\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Merge a branch into the current branch.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-dry\-run
Preview merge without modifying the working tree
.TP
.BR \\\-s, \\\-\\\-strategy \\fI<strategy>\\fR
Conflict resolution strategy: semantic, ours, theirs, manual (default: semantic)
.TP
.BR \\\-C \\fI<REPO_PATH>\\fR
Run as if suture was started in <path>
.TP
.BR \\\-h, \\\-\\\-help
Print help
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
suture merge feature       # Merge feature into current branch
suture merge \\\-\\\-dry\-run feature  # Preview merge
suture merge \\\-s ours feature    # Auto\-resolve by keeping our version
suture merge \\\-s theirs feature  # Auto\-resolve by keeping their version
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suture (1)
